This paper discusses data anonymization techniques, which are commonly used in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper specifically focuses on privacy breaches, which is a topic within the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of quantitative algorithms to evaluate privacy breaches, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of information theory (cs.IT) as it relates to the concept of privacy.
